# ── Gotchas & decisions ────────────────────────────────────
@gotcha|issue:CDC slot bloat|detail:Debezium replication slots grow unbounded if consumer falls behind; WAL retention can fill disk and crash Postgres|fix:Monitor pg_replication_slots; set max_slot_wal_keep_size; alert on replication lag > 1 GB
@gotcha|issue:Schema evolution breaks Spark|detail:Adding a non-nullable column in source DB causes Spark Iceberg merge to fail with schema mismatch|fix:All CDC schema changes must be nullable-first; run schema compatibility check in CI before deploy
@gotcha|issue:Snowflake cost spikes|detail:Ad-hoc Looker explores on large tables can spin up XL warehouses; monthly bill spiked 3x in Q3|fix:Per-user warehouse size caps; resource monitors with auto-suspend; query complexity guardrails in Looker

@decision|id:ADR-031|title:Iceberg over Delta Lake for raw/curated|status:accepted|reason:Vendor-neutral table format; works across Spark, Trino, Snowflake without lock-in
@decision|id:ADR-032|title:Debezium CDC over batch extracts|status:accepted|reason:Sub-minute latency for production data; batch extracts were 6h stale and caused reconciliation bugs
@decision|id:ADR-033|title:dbt for SQL transforms, Spark for heavy compute|status:accepted|reason:dbt gives analysts self-serve; Spark handles joins over 500M+ rows where dbt/Snowflake times out

@component|name:Airflow DAGs|file:orchestration/dags/|does:Schedules all batch ETL; ~80 DAGs across ingestion, transform, export
@component|name:dbt Project|file:transform/dbt_project/|does:200+ models organized as staging -> intermediate -> marts
@component|name:Great Expectations|file:quality/great_expectations/|does:Data quality suites for row counts, nulls, referential integrity, freshness

@config|param:kafka.retention.ms|value:604800000|note:7-day retention on raw topics for replay
@config|param:spark.executor.memory|value:8g|note:Tuned for Iceberg merge workloads
@config|param:snowflake.warehouse.auto_suspend|value:60|note:Suspend idle warehouses after 60s

@entry|use-case:Daily batch pipeline|command:Airflow triggers at 02:00 UTC -> Spark raw-to-curated -> dbt marts -> Looker cache warm
@entry|use-case:Real-time clickstream|command:Segment -> Kafka -> S3 raw (5 min micro-batch) -> Spark streaming -> curated

@note|context:cost|text:Snowflake accounts for 60% of data platform spend; Iceberg queries via Trino are 4x cheaper for internal analytics
@note|context:compliance|text:PII scanner runs nightly; any new PII column auto-tagged and access-restricted within 24 h via Lake Formation
